{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637167","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637167"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:38:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:38:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17635"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17635","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17635"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.44,0.04,0.52,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10349"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116563"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10349","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10349"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2024-12-20T12:34:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-29T21:04:17+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2024-12-20T12:37:06+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-30 14:43:25"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17635"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"15138"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98556"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10012"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24208"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24209"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24213"},{"type":"contributions","id":"50163"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98556"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116563","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116563"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThere are several steps in the process of the gastric phase of digestion.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary stimulus?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Visual and olfactory food cues","Food passing down the oesophagus","Food entering and distending the stomach","Protein breakdown products in the duodenum","Fatty acids in the small intestine"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThere are three phases of gastric secretion:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECephalic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGastric\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIntestinal\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe thought, \u003Cstrong\u003Esight or smell of food\u003C/strong\u003E initiates gastric secretion. This is the cephalic phase or primary stimulus and is mediated through the vagus nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFood passing down the oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E is not a recognised stimulus of gastric secretion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epresence and distension of food in the stomach\u003C/strong\u003E is the stimulus that initiates the gastric phase of digestion. This phase accounts for approximately 70% of total gastric secretion and involves both neural and hormonal mechanisms. During this phase, food in the stomach activates mechanical and chemical receptors. This triggers local neural reflexes and stimulates G cells to release gastrin, which promotes acid secretion from parietal cells and enzyme secretion from chief cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe intestinal phase is brought on when there are \u003Cstrong\u003Eprotein breakdown products in the duodenum\u003C/strong\u003E. The presence of \u003Cstrong\u003Efatty acids in the small intestine\u003C/strong\u003E inhibit gastric secretion during the intestinal phase\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastric secretion can start before the gastric phase of digestion.","The gastric phase of digestion is triggered by food entering the stomach and accounts for about 70% of gastric secretion.","Gastrin release from G cells is the primary hormonal mediator of the gastric phase.","Local neural reflexes and mechanical distension contribute to gastric secretion during the gastric phase."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98556"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17635"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98556","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98556"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-29T21:04:09+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-29T21:05:05+09:30","number":5,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2025-09-29T21:04:15+09:30","plagiarismScore":0,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-10349-5.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250930%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250930T090858Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=33989919c4f5e2445384fd72ed308bb6a45ad4d6af20e4f384254260487838da"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10349"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116563"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"descrip